Today, I'm showing you how I make my favorite, go-to smoothie that I’ve made for years! It's super easy, healthy, and I stay full for hours after drinking it. Comment below if you try it out! Also, stay tuned for a new episode next week!

RECIPE:
8 ounces milkadamia or favorite milk
1 scoop protein powder
3-4 ounces frozen acai puree
1 handful fresh spinach
3-6-9 Omega blend
2 tbsp hemp seeds

Enjoy!

I know so many people are more in need than ever this year and there’s so many people, organizations, charities & ministries you can give or donate to. 
I just had to make a video to shout out @jamesstorehouse and all the incredibly sweet people that I met today that work there. Their hearts are for trafficked and foster children, from infants to the foster teens who have aged out of foster care (who have turned 18 and now out of the foster system). 
*Also, if you are a teen in a foster home in the LA area & are in need of clothes, shoes, hygiene, beauty products or even home goods...please ask your social worker about getting in contact with @jamesstorehouse 
And if you’re in the LA area (they are near Thousand Oaks) and feel it’s on your heart to donate anything to them please go get info on their page...they are total sweethearts💕
Whatever you have to give, whether anything to donate or loving words...there are hearts in need of everything right now. Just pour love in any way you can into the world around you❤️💕 #foster #fosteringsaveslives #jamesstorehouse

node.text:
I know not everyone may need this, but maybe you can share it with someone who does. My heart has hurt that so many people I know have lost loved ones & my DM’s are filled with stories of loss💔😢

I just want to share a few things that helped me with the loss of a loved one:
1. I decided to live each day bigger, enjoy each sunset more, live bolder, braver and live the very most of each day, in honor of my dad.

2. Find ways to laugh. When my head and eyes were in almost excruciating pain from crying non-stop, I would watch comedy specials at night to give my brain and heart a break from crying and fall asleep to. Laughter is an incredible way to help handle the worst of times.

3. If you feel you had things you wanted to tell someone that has moved to heaven, you can write a letter, so your mind and heart feel like they got all the things they wanted to express out.✨

4. This doesn’t get talked about much but the pain in the morning when you wake up & your brain remembers, and you don’t want to be awake. This initial shock and sting when you wake up, fades away. It only lasts during the initial grieving period and will lessen until it doesn’t happen anymore. I just want to you to know it doesn’t last for always❤️ you’ll always miss them but that shocking pain won’t always hurt like that.

5. I want you to know you’re not alone. That helped me feel like I could make it, if others had too. We can all live bigger, make holidays beautiful and festive in their honor, to make them proud.

I hope just one person felt comfort from this. I hope someone felt a spark of hope to live bigger and live more out of each day in honor of your precious loved one waiting in heaven.  I pray you feel the comfort & hope of heaven like the warmest, biggest hug, wrapping you up in love & hope, knowing you have a huge heavenly hug, waiting for you, forever. And that sparkles of hope, comfort & love from heaven start to sparkle up heavenly wonder and love, like sunshine-on-your-heart gifts, blessing your day, direct from heaven and God and your loved one❤️✨

Life is short but heaven is forever❤️

I hope you can feel my love & the hug I wish I could give to every hurting heart❤️

He was silently fighting cancer and undergoing chemo & surgeries in between filming movies. 
He is what a true inspiration and super hero is...he’s left a legacy of inspiring words, a legacy of work he fought to make sure was inspiring and positive. 
No one knew the battles he was fighting. No one knows that battles that most of us are dealing with. Be kinder to everyone, more understanding. Offer more love, instead of judgement. People judged him for losing weight, accusing him of many things, to the point he removed a video where people comments were just awful. None of them knew he was so thin due to the cancer. Cancer may have taken him too soon from this world, be he leaves behind a legacy of positivity, kindness, heart and inspiration. His hope was beyond what this world has to offer✨ And #ChadwickBoseman is and will continue to inspire the world all the way from heaven, with his heart and legacy❤️

If you feel like all hope is gone, nothing is working out, your dreams are over or you don’t see how anything will work out...I hope something in this video encourages your heart. I am taking off my makeup & telling a little bit of my life story, you might not know...about my life, how I got started on youtube, how I feel about drama, and working with Kim Kardashian. The video also ends with me crying and have zero makeup on...so there’s that bonus. 
But I hope more than anything, something in here, inspires you to keep going. 
Your greatest failure, feeling like nothing could possibly work out, might be the exact place you need to be, to launch, start, or pull you backwards so far, it’s just how you be catapulted farther to your next big blessing! I’m cheering you on...NEVER GIVE UP! 
Exactly 1 year ago, yesterday, this video went live on @entertainmenttonight and I am glad they asked me to share my story and heart in hopes that it will touch your heart and a courage your story ❤️#motivation #inspiration and some #throwbackthursday

(Please feel free to share💕to reach more people to share her story & message) 93 year old, Opal Lee, is walking 2.5 miles a day, from Texas to Washington DC, in honor of the 2.5 years it took to get the message of the Emancipation Proclamation, to end slavery in the US, which was signed, January 1, 1863, to finally get to the last slaves in Texas. June 19th, 1865, known as Juneteenth, marks the day those slaves received word 2.5 years later, that they were finally free.
We can be unified, blacks & non-blacks, to join Opal I. Getting congress to make this a federally recognized holiday in ALL 50 states. 
We as Americans, can come together and honor this day, that the last of the slaves were finally able to be set free❤️ No matter the color of your skin, your ethnic background, we can all come together and celebrate the end of slavery and the last of the slaves finally being free❤️ #juneteenth

Super fast, easy & fun hair tutorial! WHAT YOU NEED: need a large barrel curling iron, colored fabric strips or colored string or cord, dry shampoo (we used my Mermaid Dust Dry Shampoo from @ogx_beauty), tiny clear elastics & metal hair braid cuffs.
Then celebrity hairstylist @jesushair applied dry shampoo to give it volume & texture, he wrapped hair in sections around iron barrel & twisted the hair as it curled to make it more lived-in looking. Then he took sections to braid and looped it around top section of hair and braided it in with the braid. His finished the look by applying metal hair braid cuffs on the top and bottom of braids. This look was so fun, easy and perfect for any day you want to try it or for when music festivals are a thing again! Tag me if you try it! We've got some extra SUPER STRAIGHT PRO HAIR TIPS & TRICKS to get the sleekest, smoothest, straightest hair.
Here’s the tutorial I did with @maneaddicts and @emmawillismakeup 
STEP 1. Wash & Moisturize Hair With a Good Hydrating Shampoo & Conditioner to help smooth it and tame frizzy, dryness or damage. 
I used my @ogx_beauty HUGS Shampoo & Kisses Conditioner, then I applied the Mermaid Mask as a deep conditioner to the ends. 
STEP 2. Apply a product to help smooth hair and protect against heat from the hot tools. Emma used the Shea Sleek Smooth Styling Spray to protect the hair up to 450 degrees.

STEP 3. Blow dry hair like regular with a large round brush.

STEP 4. Brush the hair to smooth it before applying flat iron, so you don’t iron the tangles or knots into the hair. Glide the flat iron slowly from roots to tips.

STEP 5. Go back in with Shea Sleek Smooth Styling Spray to the very ends and then really taper the ends with the flat iron, to get them really straight and pin-pointy smooth.

STEP 6. Last step, use a hairspray, Emma spritzed the top part of the hair and around the face, with the Shea Sleek Humidity Blocking Hair Spray from OGX, then smoothed all flyaways and unruly hairs down with the bottle and around the face she used her fingers.

RECIPE:
8 ounces milkadamia or favorite milk
1 scoop protein powder
3-4 ounces frozen acai puree
1 handful fresh spinach
3-6-9 Omega blend
2 tbsp hemp seeds

Enjoy!

…I’m 43 (now) and have been doing makeup for over 20 years. Started esthetician school over 20 years ago, finished doing cosmetology and began my career as a freelance makeup artist over 2 decades ago. And probably been perfecting the nose contour for a good 27-28 years!😂
So thought I’d post a lil’ “this is what makeup at 43 looks like” 😂…it’s crazy I’ve been doing makeup longer than most TikTokers & Influencers have been alive🙈😂🙈

SONG: It’s Been Way Too Long
ARTIST: @annemarie & @nathandawe

Thankful to be alive for another birthday and thankful to my mama for having me, to even have a birthday! This is what 43 looks like and my mama is 62! 

Thank you for every loving birthday message, wish and comment…you don’t know your words have meant to my heart. Grateful to be alive another day, year and birthday❤️🙏 And happy birthday to all my other July babies this month! ❤️

📸: Ellie took both these picture. She said we needed a picture right here, and they came out better than all the other pictures we took!

Thank you all for letting me know about this. I’m not sure how quick I’ll be getting answers or responses, but I will try to update you on my stories as soon as I can.
Again, thank you all for reaching out to let me know. I know those of you who follow me closely, know I’ve been going through some things and have just barely started posted more regularly to my stories. As some of you guys know I have a collab with OGX in stores now, and though this doesn’t pertain to those products, this is shocking to me to find out about this. And again, thank you for letting me know about this and thank you for all your love and just caring about me in any way❤️

Not your regular leopard print…
Glitter foiled & Candyland  colored! These are my official birthday (not til the 9th) nails!

My good friend @sohotrightnail blows my mind with her ability to do any idea I come up with! I was like “what if we do, leopard print but glitter spots?”…she just says yes and points me to her wall of glitter foils! She had painted the black leopard squiggles (you know I’m a sucker for leopard print)! And she patiently puts up with my endless, color combo selecting! Plus I just get to hang out and laugh with my amazingly talented friend! I love you Bel❤️ 
thanks for giving me cool nails to show everyone😘 #nails #nailsofinstagram #nailsoftheday #nailsdesign #leopardnails #glitternails #trendynails #nailinspo #coolnails

node.text:
In case anyone wondered how I looked yesterday for the 4th of July…

I did my makeup (this is THEE most makeup I’ve worn outside my house in a whiiiiiiile) and chose to highlight my “big business” forehead by pulling my hair away to let the world know…we love a large forehead and aren’t afraid to show it😂
(Please feel free to zoom on my forehead crinkles as well)…

I thought a red lip might be overkill.

I wasn’t gonna post a picture, but since I haven’t posted as much as normal recently (I’ve just been going through a hard time) …I thought I might as well slap this up here and it’s my birthday in 4 days, so I’m trying to amp up the festive feelings✨🎉
